@CARD DESIGN-PRGRPH
 PROCEDURE DIVISION.
 CLAUDE SECTION.

 DESIGN-PRGRPH.
* THE SITE COMPILES FROM A SMALL HAND-WRITTEN TEXT FORMAT
* (.PCOB) INTO WHAT THE RENDERER NEEDS - NO CMS, NO RICH-TEXT
* EDITOR, NO GENERATED MARKUP.

* ADVANTAGE: SEBASTIAN CAN EDIT WORDING OR ADD A CARD WITHOUT
* TOUCHING TYPESCRIPT. NAV, LINKS AND ROW COUNTS ARE ALL
* DERIVED FROM THE TEXT, NOT HAND-MAINTAINED SEPARATELY.

* DISADVANTAGE: THE 80-COLUMN CARD IS RIGID BY DESIGN. LONG
* PROSE - A BLOG POST, SAY - DOESN'T FIT THIS SHAPE WITHOUT
* A DIFFERENT FORMAT ALONGSIDE IT. STILL AN OPEN QUESTION.

* GOBACK TO PROCEDURE DIVISION CLAUDE SECTION
     {{link:claude}}EXIT PARAGRAPH{{/link}}
     .

